CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 24, 1958, pg. 3, reads: " 'Not Worried' - Smiling Matthew S. Anderson, above, was snapped on Tuesday after he had visited polling place at McKelvy School. Asked whether the voting trend favored or oposed [opposed] him, his two-word reply was: "Not worried." - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Matthew S. Anderson wearing cross patterned bow tie, standing outside of McKelvy School
